<li id="cite_note-34"><b><a href="#cite_ref-34" title="">^</a></b> Bobadilla's 48-page report—derived from the testimonies of 23 people who had seen or heard about the treatment meted out by Columbus and his brothers—had originally been lost for centuries, but was rediscovered in 2005 in the Spanish archives in <a href="/wiki/Valladolid" title="Valladolid">Valladolid</a>. It contained an account of Columbus's seven-year reign as the first <a href="/w/index.php?title=Governor_of_the_Indies&amp;action=edit&amp;redlink=1" class="new" title="Governor of the Indies (page does not exist)">Governor of the Indies</a>.</li>
