<li id="cite_note-remains-39"><b><a href="#cite_ref-remains_39-0" title="">^</a></b> <cite style="font-style:normal" class="news" id="CITEREFLorenzi2004">Lorenzi, Rossella (October 6, 2004). <a href="http://dsc.discovery.com/news/briefs/20041004/columbus.html" class="external text" title="http://dsc.discovery.com/news/briefs/20041004/columbus.html" rel="nofollow">"DNA Suggests Columbus Remains in Spain"</a>. <a href="/wiki/Discovery_Channel" title="Discovery Channel">Discovery News</a><span class="printonly">. <a href="http://dsc.discovery.com/news/briefs/20041004/columbus.html" class="external free" title="http://dsc.discovery.com/news/briefs/20041004/columbus.html" rel="nofollow">http://dsc.discovery.com/news/briefs/20041004/columbus.html</a></span><span class="reference-accessdate">. Retrieved on 2006-10-11</span>.</cite><span class="Z3988" title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=bookitem&amp;rft.btitle=DNA+Suggests+Columbus+Remains+in+Spain&amp;rft.atitle=&amp;rft.aulast=Lorenzi&amp;rft.aufirst=Rossella&amp;rft.au=Lorenzi%2C+Rossella&amp;rft.date=October+6%2C+2004&amp;rft.pub=%5B%5BDiscovery+Channel%7CDiscovery+News%5D%5D&amp;rft_id=http%3A%2F%2Fdsc.discovery.com%2Fnews%2Fbriefs%2F20041004%2Fcolumbus.html&amp;rfr_id=info:sid/en.wikipedia.org:Christopher_Columbus"><span style="display: none;">&#160;</span></span></li>
<li id="cite_note-40"><b><a href="#cite_ref-40" title="">^</a></b> <a href="http://www.msnbc.msn.com/id/12871458/" class="external text" title="http://www.msnbc.msn.com/id/12871458/" rel="nofollow">DNA verifies Columbus’ remains in Spain</a>, <i><a href="/wiki/Associated_Press" title="Associated Press">Associated Press</a></i>, May 19, 2006</li>
<li id="cite_note-dugard-41"><b><a href="#cite_ref-dugard_41-0" title="">^</a></b> Dugard, Martin. The Last Voyage of Columbus. Little, Brown and Company: New York, 2005.</li>
<li id="cite_note-42"><b><a href="#cite_ref-42" title="">^</a></b> <cite style="font-style:normal" class="book" id="CITEREFStewart1967"><a href="/wiki/George_R._Stewart" title="George R. Stewart">Stewart, George R.</a> (1967) [1945]. <i>Names on the Land: A Historical Account of Place-Naming in the United States</i> (Sentry edition (3rd) ed.). <a href="/wiki/Houghton_Mifflin" title="Houghton Mifflin">Houghton Mifflin</a>. pp.&#160;199.</cite><span class="Z3988" title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=book&amp;rft.btitle=Names+on+the+Land%3A+A+Historical+Account+of+Place-Naming+in+the+United+States&amp;rft.aulast=Stewart&amp;rft.aufirst=George+R.&amp;rft.au=Stewart%2C+George+R.&amp;rft.date=1967&amp;rft.pages=pp.%26nbsp%3B199&amp;rft.edition=Sentry+edition+%283rd%29&amp;rft.pub=%5B%5BHoughton+Mifflin%5D%5D&amp;rfr_id=info:sid/en.wikipedia.org:Christopher_Columbus"><span style="display: none;">&#160;</span></span></li>
<li id="cite_note-43"><b><a href="#cite_ref-43" title="">^</a></b> Morison, Samuel Eliot <i>Admiral of the Ocean Sea: A Life of Christopher Columbus</i>, pg. 47-48, Boston 1942.</li>
<li id="cite_note-44"><b><a href="#cite_ref-44" title="">^</a></b> Bartolomé de Las Casas, <i>Historia de las Indias</i>, ed. Agustín Millares Carlo, 3 vols. (Mexico City, 1951), book 1, chapter 2, 1:29. <i>The Spanish word garzos is now usually translated as "light blue," but it seems to have connoted light grey-green or hazel eyes to Columbus's contemporaries. The word rubio can mean "blonde," "fair," or "ruddy." The Worlds of Christopher Columbus</i> by William D. &amp; Carla Rahn Phillips, pg. 282.</li>
<li id="cite_note-45"><b><a href="#cite_ref-45" title="">^</a></b> <cite style="font-style:normal" class="web"><a href="http://www.christopher-columbus.eu/dna-tests.htm" class="external text" title="http://www.christopher-columbus.eu/dna-tests.htm" rel="nofollow">"DNA Tests on the bones of Christopher Columbus' bones, on his relatives and on Genoese and Catalin claimaints"</a><span class="printonly">. <a href="http://www.christopher-columbus.eu/dna-tests.htm" class="external free" title="http://www.christopher-columbus.eu/dna-tests.htm" rel="nofollow">http://www.christopher-columbus.eu/dna-tests.htm</a></span><span class="reference-accessdate">. Retrieved on 2009-02-09</span>.</cite><span class="Z3988" title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=bookitem&amp;rft.btitle=DNA+Tests+on+the+bones+of+Christopher+Columbus%27+bones%2C+on+his+relatives+and+on+Genoese+and+Catalin+claimaints&amp;rft.atitle=&amp;rft_id=http%3A%2F%2Fwww.christopher-columbus.eu%2Fdna-tests.htm&amp;rfr_id=info:sid/en.wikipedia.org:Christopher_Columbus"><span style="display: none;">&#160;</span></span></li>
